<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-732-090  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 732 090.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 2 1989 v6 n39 p25(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Program lets inkjet, dot printers emulate HP's LaserJet Series II.andO;(Metro Software's LaserTwin 2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metro Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   LaserTwin 2.0 (Utility program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionEmulationDot-Matrix PrintersInk-Jet PrintersLaser PrintersCompatible SoftwareUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Program Lets Inkjet, Dot Printers Emulate HP's LaserJet Series IIandM;TUCSON, Ariz.andP;  -- Metro Software has announced a LaserJet Series II emulationpackage for inkjet and dot matrix printers.andM;LaserTwin version 2.0 provides Hewlett-Packard LaserJet Series II emulationfor approximately 90 different kinds of injet and dot matrix printers, saidMetro co-founder and LaserTwin developer Richard Wallat.andM;A special version of LaserTwin is available for DEC's LN03 printer and forthe Canon Laser Beam printer, he said.andM;LaserTwin is RAM-resident and occupies 26KB of memory, according to Wallat.andO;&quot;Emulation is active as output is sent to the printer, providing liveinterpretation,&quot; Wallat said.andM;LaserTwin users can run all software designed for Hewlett-Packard's LaserJetSeries II and, with the addition of Metro's SuperFonts 25/1 software, can useall of the font symbol sets that are built into the HP series, according toWallat.andM;The emulation also allows HP's DeskJet, 24-pin and 9-pin printers to produceprintouts in landscape orientation.andM;The program has an embedded text command language.andP;  &quot;With our commandlanguage, you are able to address any point on the page in any order,&quot; Wallatsaid.andP;  Users can create simple scripts to produce reports, headers, footers,labels, page overlays and other features commonly associated with desktoppublishing packages.andM;LaserTwin does not require additional hardware to achieve HP LaserJet SeriesII emulation, according to company officials.andM;LaserTwin can drive 24-pin dot matrix printers at a resolution of 360 dotsper inch, company officials said.andM;Users with HP laser, injet and dot matrix printers can install and run all oftheir software with the HP LaserJet Series II driver, company officialsnoted.andM;For background printing, LaserTwin includes a spooler, officials said.andM;In order to run LaserTwin, a user must have an IBM PC, XT, AT or compatible,DOS 2.0 or higher and a hard disk.andP;  Application software using LaserTwin mustinclude an HP Laser Series II print driver.andM;LaserTwin version 2.0 is available now and is priced at $149.andP;  After December31 it will be priced at $179.andP;  SuperFonts 25/1 is available now and is pricedat $179.andM;For more information, Metro Software Inc. can be contacted at 2509 N.andO;Campbell Ave., Suite 214, Tucson, AZ 85719, (602) 292-0313.andO;</TEXT></DOC>